summary:
Behind the Scenes of Day of the Doctor (Part 10)

  Excerpt from this BBC interview with Steven Moffat: The 50th special will...
caption:
Behind the Scenes of Day of the Doctor (Part 10)

Excerpt from this BBC interview with Steven Moffat:

The 50th special will mark the return of David Tennant to the role of the Tenth Doctor, starring opposite the Eleventh, Matt Smith. How was it having two Doctors on set?

It was eye twisting at times. You don’t quite realise how these two men have become hard wired into your brain as the Doctor. Matt and David got on so well and their interaction on screen is a sublime double act. Matt said to me, “It’s a bit like Laurel and Laurel. It’s like Hardy didn’t turn up”. They are absolutely great together. Sometimes very, very, different - other times, in moments they choose together, they are exactly the same.

And seeing Billie and David on set together, how was that?

Seeing Billie and David standing on set together was quite epic. Billie told me that as she is very good friends with both Matt and David, she felt quite torn and divided. She didn’t know how to deal with both of them at the same time, so if she was talking to one, she would stroke the arm of the other.

summary: I’ve been meaning to do this.  Despite my love of her: here are some of my favorite female costars of David Tennant, aside from...
body:
I’ve been meaning to do this.

Despite my love of her: here are some of my favorite female costars of David Tennant, aside from Billie Piper:

Kelly Macdonald

seen with him in The Decoy Bride

Janet Montgomery

seen with him in Spies of Warsaw

Nina Sosanya

seen with him in Casanova, Love Labour’s Lost, Doctor Who, 96 Ways to Say I Love You

Rosamund Pike

seen with him in What We Did On Our Holiday

Sarah Parish

seen with him in Blackpool, Recovery, Doctor Who, Broadchurch, You Me and Him

There are so many more incl: Krysten Ritter, Jessica Hynes, his other long terms companions as Ten (Freema and Catherine) Catherine who had been his friend pretty much the same length as Billie, who was his Beatrice to Benedick and thankfully they are working together again! Who else is excited?! There is also, Kylie Minogue who was Astrid Peth, Fenella Woolgar who was Agatha Christie. She was with him in Spies of Warsaw and an older mini series, He Knew He Was Right, Anna Gunn who was his costar in Gracepoint, Olivia Colman ofc, now he has worked with Jennifer Garner for the upcoming series Camping.

DAVID ONCE WORKED WITH DAME MAGGIE SMITH I MEAN COME ON

The list goes on.

This is not intended to bash Billie whatsoever, her and David are quite a duo. But I feel with how….enthusiastic Doctor x Rose shippers are who then take it to Teninch Fic which are seperate works by the actors…we seem to forget that in canon. David has worked with some MARVELOUS women. And I just think they deserve to have their beautiful faces showcased. I’m not blaming anyone, in fact, for a while I was guilty of the same. But with how much the acting industry has changed and grown I think it’s just important to acknowledge brilliance when it’s seen! And trust me, all these women (yes, ofc including Billie) are fantastique! x

And same can be applied for Billie.

She’s worked with Riz Ahmed, Reeve Carney, Orlando Bloom etc. So many talented actors!!!

It’s great :)

The point still remains. Teninch fic is great. I love all the AUs. But I’d love for us to take a moment to really look and appreciate these wonderous and talented women. (And men, regarding Billie I s’pose!)

Now back to the awesome xover ships, they are lovely. But so are these actresses! x

blog.name: oimatchstickman
blog.title: Manic Pixie Dream Doctors
blog.description:
A cosplayer, seamstress, and retail worker who has many fictional interests such as: Doctor Who, Phantom of the Opera, Star Trek, Marvel, Portal, Disney, Pixar, Phineas and Ferb, M*A*S*H, Les Miserables, Into the Woods, and any other fandom I feel like.

But mostly Doctor Who.

I like all the Doctor Who I've seen- including Moffat's era- and no hate is tolerated. At all. Let me and others enjoy our show without constantly picking at the smallest thing thanks.
